The manuscript states the Bartik instrument uses state-level employment by major industry sector from BLS QCEW using 10 NAICS supersectors, with base-year industry shares (2006/2019). The code instead attempts to fetch state×industry series directly from FRED using a limited and non-clearly documented set of mnemonics (initially 6 sectors; then it conditionally adds INFO/TRAD/MINE). It does not include the full set of supersectors described in the paper (e.g., Professional & Business Services appears in national series mapping but is not fetched for states here), and it is not using QCEW explicitly. This risks constructing an exposure measure that differs materially from what is described, affecting identification and reported magnitudes.: INDUSTRIES = {
    'MFG': 'Manufacturing',
    'CONS': 'Construction',
    'FIRE': 'Financial Activities',
    'LEIH': 'Leisure and Hospitality',
    'EDUH': 'Education and Health',
    'GOVT': 'Government',
}
...
# Also try INFO, TRAD, MINE with alternate patterns
for st in STATE_FIPS:
    for ind_code in ['INFO', 'TRAD', 'MINE']:
        if ind_code not in state_ind_emp[st]:
            for suffix in ['', 'N', 'ON']:
                sid = f"{st}{ind_code}{suffix}"
                s = fred_to_series(sid, "2000-01-01", "2024-06-01")
                if s is not None:
                    state_ind_emp[st][ind_code] = s
                    INDUSTRIES.setdefault(ind_code,
                        {'INFO':'Information','TRAD':'Trade/Transport','MINE':'Mining'}[ind_code])
                    break
